'Everybody's touched by it. She has so many friends and other people who just want to help her kids at this time. Her family is massive as well, so lots of support for them,' Ms Luke told Fairfax.

Ms Costigan's cousin, Nathan Costigan, confirmed that 'all of the money raised would be forwarded to the three children whose safety and wellbeing he said were the family's first priority right now'. 

'A HUGE thank you to Emma Luke who started the gofundme page for the children. I can confirm it is legit, and I am meeting my local member Nicole Lawder MLA to source legal advice and a solicitor for the kids to ensure they receive every cent,' Mr Costigan said on Tuesday.

While more than 1,400 people have submitted donations on the page, hundreds more have offered clothing and toys after being touched by the tragedy.

'I am donating today because if my wife and I were to pass I would want to know that my little ones were looked after too. No one should have to grow up without their parents but should that happen its nice to know that society has your back,' one donor wrote.

