A fundraising walk has also been organised by the Canberra Mums Exercise Group, which Ms Costigan was a member of, for March 22.

'Tara Costigan, was murdered over the weekend. To honour her life, raise funds for her three children that are now tragically without their mother, and to stand up against domestic violence, we would like as many of you as possible to participate in the fundraising walk,' the event's organisers said.

More than 1700 people are expected to attend the walk.

